<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 23 at 10:23PM CDT  by NWS Springfield</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Cherokee County
through 1045 PM CDT...
At 1022 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Chetopa, moving northeast at 55 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Baxter Springs...                 Columbus...
Cherokee...                       Weir...
Lowell...                         Sherman...
Scammon...                        West Mineral...
Treece...                         Roseland...
Neutral...                        Melrose...
Riverton...                       Carona...
Skidmore...                       Hallowell...
Sherwin...                        Faulkner...
Stippville...                     Crestline...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
